OL,3,CStreeting poised to launch leadership
OL,4,Cbid as Starmer clings on as PM
OL,6,FStarmer is expected to fight any
OL,7,Fleadership challenge, and spent
OL,8,FWednesday afternoon meeting ministers
OL,9,Fand Labour MPs as he sought to avert a
OL,10,Fcoup.
OL,12,FAllies of the PM are reported to be
OL,13,Furging colleagues not to "plunge the
OL,14,Fparty into chaos" ` warning that a
OL,15,Fleadership contest would paralyse the
OL,16,Fgovernment for months.
OL,18,FOn Thursday, Starmer will introduce
OL,19,Flegislation overhauling social housing
OL,20,Fand the "right to buy" in an attempt
OL,21,Fto regain control of the agenda.
OL,26,@|D@IOU|D@VO]
